"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-paralympics-sarah-storey-paralympian-paris-french-para-b2606744.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  DameSarah Storeycriticised the \\\"appalling\\\" decision to have the women's C5 time trial half the distance of the men's event after winning the 18th Paralympic gold of her career atParis2024.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's most successfulParalympianovercame a 7.18 seconds deficit at the only mid-race checkpoint to stretch her record-breaking exploits in the eastern suburbs of theFrenchcapital.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the 46-year-old was delighted with her latest triumph, she bemoaned a missed opportunity for disability sport and raised the issue of gender inequality after completing a course of just 14.1 kilometres in 20 minutes and 22.15 seconds.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Storey said riders had appealed to organisers about the race length before the Games but not received a response.\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's C5 event, in which Britain's Blaine Hunt finished 11th, was double the distance, comprising two laps of the same course.\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1088, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cervical_vertebrae\", \"score\": 0.9991810337058695, \"rank\": 0.0008196373813674818, \"text\": \"C5\", \"types\": [\"Q4936952\", \"Q265868\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cervical_vertebrae\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cervical_vertebrae\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blaine_Anderson\", \"score\": 0.9952647894118013, \"rank\": 0.004757739486537487, \"text\": \"Blaine\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blaine_Anderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blaine_Anderson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is the shortest Paralympic time trial we have ever had,\\\" said Storey, who was 4.69 secs quicker than France's Heidi Gaugain.\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.742045322025147, \"rank\": 0.34650934959304497, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1326, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidi\", \"score\": 0.9999999934216248, \"rank\": 5.123988768524208e-09, \"text\": \"Heidi\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heidi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And I think it's a real shame because you do not get to showcase Para sport in the way that you want to.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I hope this is the only time it's less than 20k.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You have to ask the organisers (why it was so short).\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really hope that they never do this to the women again because I think it's been appalling  \\\"But there is plenty of time in the day for us to do two laps like the men.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And having fought so hard for parity in women's cycling, to not have it in Para cycling after what we had in Glasgow (world championships) last year is a real disappointment.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9999999417714224, \"rank\": 5.8170226402214505e-08, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have had to put that disappointment aside and just concentrate on what I can control because I could not control the race distance.\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 2037, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I really hope that they never do this to the women again because I think it's been appalling.\\\"\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2138, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The PA news agency understands organisers opted to hold some time trials over the shorter distance due to there being 19 races on Wednesday's busy schedule, in addition to medal ceremonies.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Storey wrote her name in the history books at Tokyo 2020 by claiming a trio of titles to move ahead of former swimmer Mike Kenny in the all-time list of GB athletes.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.6279320425767224, \"rank\": 0.592130540772866, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Kenny_(writer)\", \"score\": 0.8376701868197467, \"rank\": 0.1937799043061952, \"text\": \"Mike Kenny\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Kenny_(writer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Kenny_(writer)\"}, {\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9005793856669296, \"rank\": 0.11034795669647371, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The time trial inJapanwas held over a distance of 24km.\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Storey won that event by a far more commanding margin of one minute and 31.9 secs and expects to race a minimum of 22km at championships.\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the ninth Games of a remarkable career which started in the swimming pool at Barcelona in 1992, she further cemented her legacy as husband Barney and children Louisa and Charlie watched on.\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2773, \"end\": 2782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"score\": 0.8185638070612913, \"rank\": 0.16636918583811722, \"text\": \"Barcelona\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barcelona\"}, {\"begin\": 2835, \"end\": 2841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Stinson\", \"score\": 0.9999999927849785, \"rank\": 6.466526758881477e-09, \"text\": \"Barney\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Stinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Stinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver medallist Gaugain led at the 5.8km mark in Clichy-sous-bois before being overhauled, while Australian rider Alana Forster finished third.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clichy-sous-bois\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\"}, {\"begin\": 2985, \"end\": 2995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9993849299113297, \"rank\": 0.0005727619939668078, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 3008, \"end\": 3015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._M._Forster\", \"score\": 0.9999998431185427, \"rank\": 1.568806543141016e-07, \"text\": \"Forster\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._M._Forster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._M._Forster\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Storey's victory maintains her 100 per cent Games record on the bike, which began at Beijing in 2008 and now spans 13 races, to take her overall Paralympic medal tally to 29, including 16 in the pool.\", \"from\": 3033, \"to\": 3233, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3118, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999931992534, \"rank\": 6.800714612317698e-09, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(I am) on top of the world,\\\" she said.\\\"\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I came here to try and get the gold medal (in this event) for the fifth time, fourth defence and I have done it.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the perfectly-paced ride.\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was down seven seconds at the first time check, but I knew that was the easiest part of the course going into that first time check because there were quite a few descents and technical sections where you can get free speed, have a recovery and be prepared for that first climb.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a carrot knowing that I was down.\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3747, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have just got to empty the tank to the finish.\\\"\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"British rider Fran Brown backed up Storey's triumph by taking silver in the women's C1-3 time trial, in a time of 21 minutes 46.18 secs.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3801, \"end\": 3808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8004058021688094, \"rank\": 0.2442215036808423, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3815, \"end\": 3825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fran_Brown\", \"score\": 0.7999988663296304, \"rank\": 0.2499999999999138, \"text\": \"Fran Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fran_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fran_Brown\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I would have liked a bit of a longer course as well, we are capable of riding a bit further, but we all did the same course on the day so make the most of it,\\\" said Brown.\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 4111, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland's Katie-George Dunlevy later won a third successive gold in the women's B time trial, ahead of British pair Sophie Unwin and Lora Fachie.\", \"from\": 4113, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4123, \"end\": 4143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie-George_Dunlevy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie-George Dunlevy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie-George_Dunlevy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie-George_Dunlevy\"}, {\"begin\": 4216, \"end\": 4223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8004058021688094, \"rank\": 0.2442215036808423, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4229, \"end\": 4241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Unwin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Unwin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Unwin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Unwin\"}, {\"begin\": 4246, \"end\": 4257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lora_Fachie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lora Fachie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lora_Fachie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lora_Fachie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dunlevy and her tandem pilot Linda Kelly were one minute and 23.6 secs faster than silver medallists Unwin and Jenny Holl in a winning time of 38 mins and 16.58 secs, while Fachie celebrated bronze on her 36th birthday alongside Corrine Hall.\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4289, \"end\": 4300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_L._Kelly\", \"score\": 0.9999999971378202, \"rank\": 2.862307630864411e-09, \"text\": \"Linda Kelly\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_L._Kelly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Linda_L._Kelly\"}, {\"begin\": 4361, \"end\": 4366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Unwin\", \"score\": 0.9994116714896216, \"rank\": 0.0005886748446653208, \"text\": \"Unwin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Unwin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raymond_Unwin\"}, {\"begin\": 4371, \"end\": 4381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Holl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Holl\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Holl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Holl\"}, {\"begin\": 4489, \"end\": 4501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corrine_Hall\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Corrine Hall\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corrine_Hall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Corrine_Hall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4640, \"entities\": []}]}"